data.description:
Write function that return constrained value (`v`) by lower (`min`) and upper (`max`) bounds. 

It is guaranteed that given lower bound will be less or equal than upper bound (`min <= max`)

For example:
```javascript
function constrainValue(v, min, max) {
  // ... your code
}

constrainValue(5, 0, 6) === 5; // v = 5, min = 0, max = 6 
                               // => 5 is between 0 and 6
                               // answer is 5

constrainValue(-123, 0, 6) === 0; // v = -123, min = 0, max = 6 
                                  // => -123 is NOT between 0 and 6 and is less than 0 
                                  // so answer is 0 (lower bound)

constrainValue(100, 0, 6) === 6; // v = 100, min = 0, max = 6 
                                 // => 100 is NOT between 0 and 6 and is more than 6 
                                 // so answer is 6 (upper bound)
```
